Set break point:
   br <func_name>
   br <file_name>:<line_num>

Disable all break points:
   dis

Show break points:
  info br

Enable break point
  ena <break_num>

Backtrack:
  bt

Threads:
  info threads
  thread
  thread <num>
  thread apply <num> <cmd>
  thread apply all <cmd>

Watch:
  watch <expr>
  watch <expr> mask <maskvalue>

Dump memory:
  x/nfu
where:
  n: number of units
  f: format (x for hex)
  u: unit (b for byte)

E.g.: x/16xw <start_addr>
- dump 16 words in hex starting at the given address

E.g.: x/1000s <start_addr>
- dump 1000 chars

# Dump memory to file:
dump [format] [filename] [start_addr] [stop_addr]
format : binary, ihex, srec, ...

# extract video log from core file
dump binary memory video.log.p1 video_log->log_buf+video_log->idx+1 video_log->buf+video_log->log_size-1
dump binary memory video.log.p2 video_log->log_buf video_log->log_buf+video_log->idx

# Check assembly code
disassemble /m <function>

# Dump registers
info reg
